This action I commenced, men of Athens, upon no other ground than the report of Lampis, who denied that Phormio had shipped the goods or paid him the money.
Don't sup­ pose, men of Athens, that I am so senseless, so utterly mad, as to have drawn such a plaint as this, when Lampis (who must have disproved my case) admitted that he had received the money.
